Orders to establish contact with the race from beyond this world. What plans will our once brothers derive next? I will see that Ispar Elysatah receives this report. Thank you.
Farewell budhi.
FirstContact_OrdersGiven

They wished to ally with Aerbax? Going back to the atua ngamaru that began all the problems for the Tonk... I am sorry for my brothers. I fear they may be beyond salvation. I will see that Ispar Elysatah is informed of this discovery.
Farewell budhi.
FirstContact_OrdersGiven
Interesting. It appears as though they modeled their fortress after Candeth Keep. How could they have done such a thing without the original designs? I will inform Ispar Elysatah of these findings.
Farewell budhi.
FirstContact_OrdersGiven

I do not understand how such things could have occurred. These are the exact prints that were used when creating Candeth Keep. They had gone missing. Now they are found being spirited to the race from beyond. For what fell purpose? I will see that Ispar Elysatah hears of this.
Farewell budhi.

Foul beasts. They mean to make war on us all and overwhelm this world for what appears to be Wharu. They claim they have begun to change the burnt lands; the desert I think? Be wary of this foe. I fear that they will arrive in greater waves.
Farewell budhi.

I have seen such things before. These are stones carried by Mosswarts, and given to others as a gesture of gratitude. Clearly you have done some kind deed for one of their kin. Take it and display it with pride.
Your skill in negotiating with a warlike creature should be known to all. I will give you a token - if you wish to be known henceforth as a diplomat, simply hand the token back to me.
Let it be known to all that you are a Diplomat!

I recognize this. I have seen these stones carried by Mosswarts who are in mourning. I have heard that the Mosswarts have been driven from the Blackmire, and that the survivors carry these stones in memory of their lost kin.
There is a dark cloud over this stone. I sense that its owner came to you for help, and you failed him or betrayed him in some way. Take it away from me.
This I do not recognize.
I am disturbed. The keh do not recognize this idol. Was this taken from the newcomers? It is a thing that has never before been seen on this world. Please, keep it.
A vile beast! What villainy lurks in the hearts of these creatures! There is no word in the Tonk language to describe the atrocity that these beasts can manage.
It appears that the rumors that have been spreading through Elysatah's court could well be true.
Aun Laokhe sighs.

Apparently there has been some activity in the Direlands Swamp in an area once populated heavily by the Mosswarts. The Mosswarts have reached out and asked us for assistance, as you might know. Bleeargh, an emissary that sought out your people recently, went before Elysatah and asked for assistance. She told the Mosswart that they would afford him passage so long as he and his tribe remained peaceful.
I speak of this because many believe that the Mosswart exodus is related to the increase of the  Burun, especially in the direlands. I think that it would be better for me to write this down for you.
BurunIngressDirelands
Please, look into this matter for all our sakes.
Interestingly, I do not sense the rage within this creature that I do in his brother. He appears decidedly confused. Perhaps there is hope to sway him to our cause of peace...
This appears to be a potent spell. The spirits have told me how to craft it into a readable version.

Hail budhi, I come from the council chambers of Ispar Elysatah with a request. She bids that willing souls investigate the origin of the dark magics that spread across Osteth and Palenqual. She has heard that new anima have spread from the place where the kah took place. Should you find anything of note, I would like to see it. I will be calling on the keh of the Nuuani for aid to understand the things you find. Ispar Elysatah wishes to reach a peaceful accord with this new Xuta.
Should you find any odd writing that the other translators cannot decipher, perhaps the keh of the Nuuani will help decipher those as well.
